SIMPLE: debauchery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Debauchery
<hw>De*bauch"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Debaucheries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Corruption of fidelity; seduction from virtue, duty, or
allegiance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The republic of Paris will endeavor to complete the
<qex>debauchery</qex> of the army.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive indulgence of the appetites; especially,
excessive indulgence of lust; intemperance; sensuality; habitual
lewdness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Oppose . . . <qex>debauchery</qex> by temperance.</q>
<rj><qau>Sprat.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Debauchment</ent>⟦br⟧
